General.Name: Corline Biomedical AB
General.Description: Corline Biomedical AB develops, manufactures, and markets heparin based solutions to enhance kidney transplantation, cell therapies, and regenerative medicine applications. Its products are based on Corline Heparin Conjugate (CHC) technology, a heparin conjugate that is used as stand-alone pharmaceutical compound. The company's products include Renaparin for use in the treatment of end stage renal failure; Cytoparin, a cell therapy that is used for the treatment of patients with type 1 diabetes; CHC, which is used for the treatment of soft tissue injuries; medical devices; and CHS, a coronary stent use for the treatment of acute or threatened vessel closure during coronary angioplasty. The company was incorporated in 1991 and is based in Uppsala, Sweden.
